---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Offdesk Closeout Guide - Forager"
  description="Generate a dry-run closeout plan, cleanup manifest, commercial review packet, and Ondesk return package before resuming work after offdesk automation."
>
  <Nav />

  <article class="pt-32 pb-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose-content">
      <header class="mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-6 leading-tight">Offdesk Closeout Guide</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
          Offdesk work is not complete when a background task exits. It is complete after artifacts, document updates, cleanup candidates, and Ondesk return context have been reviewed.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>The Lifecycle Gate</h2>
        <pre><code>Ondesk closeout -&gt; Offdesk execution -&gt; Offdesk closeout -&gt; Ondesk return</code></pre>
        <p>
          The TUI surfaces completed tasks that still need closeout as operator attention. Run closeout before using a resumed or fresh Ondesk harness to continue the project.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Run Closeout</h2>
        <pre><code>forager offdesk closeout --project-key twinpaper --dry-run</code></pre>
        <p>
          The command writes a closeout artifact directory under the active profile:
        </p>
        <pre><code>offdesk_closeouts/&lt;timestamp&gt;_&lt;closeout-id&gt;/
  closeout_plan.json
  CLOSEOUT_PLAN.md
  cleanup_manifest.json
  COMMERCIAL_REVIEW_PACKET.md
  RETURN_PACKAGE.md</code></pre>
        <p>
          This is a dry-run planner. It does not move, delete, archive, or mutate project files.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Record Review</h2>
        <p>
          Generating the packet is not the same as approving the closeout. After reviewing the commercial packet, record the verdict:
        </p>
        <pre><code>forager offdesk closeout-review \
  --closeout-id &lt;closeout-id&gt; \
  --verdict approved \
  --reviewer gpt-5.5 \
  --review-provider gpt-5.5 \
  --review-file &lt;path-to-review-output&gt;</code></pre>
        <p>
          Only an approved review record clears the TUI closeout-required signal. Revise and blocked verdicts remain evidence but keep the return path reviewable.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Cleanup Policy</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Keep:</strong> provenance anchors, result artifacts, reports, declared task artifacts, and files needed for Ondesk return.</li>
          <li><strong>Archive candidate:</strong> raw logs and bulky runtime artifacts that may be moved only after review.</li>
          <li><strong>Delete candidate:</strong> disabled by default in the first closeout surface.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Any future move, archive, or delete action must pass commercial model review and explicit human approval through the normal approval path. Recording a closeout review still does not apply file operations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Never Auto-Mutate</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>git-tracked source or documentation files;</li>
          <li>human-authored notes or reports;</li>
          <li>hidden config, env, symlink, mount, external drive, or system paths;</li>
          <li>artifacts referenced by reports, wiki candidates, approvals, or resume records.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Ondesk Return</h2>
        <p>
          Use <code>RETURN_PACKAGE.md</code> to start the next Ondesk harness. Read the listed result artifacts first, inspect open decisions, and run the verification commands before continuing work.
        </p>
        <p>
          Pair this with the <a href="/guides/offdesk-morning-review/">Offdesk Morning Review Workflow</a> when reviewing overnight work.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>

  <Footer />
</Base>
